  "texts": [
    "They have developed five distinct types of instructions: generating solutions to novel problems, inventing with contrasting cases, comparing and contrasting, self-explanation prompts, and metacognitive questions.",
    "These methods have proven to be effective in enhancing the learning process.",
    "Additionally, Smy and colleagues (Smy et al., 2016) highlight that novices often overlook rigorous sense-making activities while solving a task and instead, directly proceed to formulate a solution.",
    "These sense-making activities, which are integral to problemsolving and learning, encompass defining the problem, structuring, representing the problem, and generating potential alternatives along with the preferred solution.",
    "In this context, Berthold and colleagues also point out that organization and elaboration are two relevant cognitive strategies during learning (Berthold & M. Nückles et al., 2007)."
  ],
